      <h2>How They Actually Differ</h2>

      <h3>Workflow</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> Browse integrated job board, get AI-tailored resume for each position, approve and auto-apply. Streamlined application workflow in one platform.</p>
      <p><strong>Careerflow.ai:</strong> Build base resume, create job-tailored versions manually, track applications, optimize LinkedIn separately. More tools but more manual steps.</p>

      <h3>Automation vs Manual Effort</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> AI tailors resumes automatically per job. Auto-apply handles submission for supported roles. You review tailored resumes (30-60 seconds) before applying.</p>
      <p><strong>Careerflow.ai:</strong> Automates resume analysis and suggestions but requires manual resume versioning. No auto-apply means manual submission for every application.</p>

      <h3>Resume Quality and Tailoring</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> Each resume is tailored to match specific job requirements with keyword optimization. Higher interview rates because applications are precisely targeted.</p>
      <p><strong>Careerflow.ai:</strong> Provides resume analysis and one-click optimizer but requires managing base vs job-tailored versions manually. Less seamless per-job customization.</p>

      <h3>Time to Value</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> See tailored resumes and applications within minutes. Auto-apply accelerates volume for remote roles.</p>
      <p><strong>Careerflow.ai:</strong> Faster initial resume setup. Value in better resumes and LinkedIn, but manual application process adds time per application.</p>

      <h3>Friction and Limitations</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> Requires reviewing each tailored resume (adds 30-60 seconds per application). Less focus on LinkedIn and networking.</p>
      <p><strong>Careerflow.ai:</strong> Base vs job-tailored resume management can be confusing. No auto-apply means manual work. Premium needed for full features. Some users report bugs.</p>
